<p>
<seg id=1> Millions of people all over Russia demonstrated against President Yeltsin on Wednesday demanding that the government make payment for wages in arrears. </seg>
<seg id=2> The actual number of people attending the demonstrations, however, was far lower than the estimate of 40 million given by organizers. </seg>
<seg id=3> A small number of demonstrators collected outside the Kremlin in Moscow, many of them waving the flag of the communist party. </seg>
<seg id=4> Presidential hopeful Alexander Lebed addressed the crowd gathered in the Siberian city of Krasnoyarsk. </seg>
<seg id=5> He said that Russian and Western investors waiting for real economic reform have waiting long enough, and are becoming impatient. </seg>
</p>
